{"type":"message","id":"e70b3248","parentId":"35006b98","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:03:50.353Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll run the workspace-janitor skill to perform a daily scan as requested by the cron job.\n\nLet me first check if there's a HEARTBEAT.md file to follow, then execute the workspace-janitor skill."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LyQWrPFQB8IAmoBjCWt1DHv1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"HEARTBEAT.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":47,"output":92,"cacheRead":14400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14539,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773079424771}}
{"type":"message","id":"b64376a9","parentId":"e70b3248","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:03:50.370Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_LyQWrPFQB8IAmoBjCWt1DHv1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\nSMART MEMORY LOADING (do this first, every heartbeat)\nBefore anything else, load context efficiently:\n Read memory/projects.md - compact project registry (~1K tokens)\n Read MEMORY.md - curated long-term memory (~3K tokens)\n Only load daily notes (memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md) when asked about specific past work\n Only run vector search when a specific question about past work comes up\nThis gives full context at ~10% of the token cost. Daily notes are archives, not runtime docs.\n\n# VECTOR MEMORY FLUSH POLICY (CHANGE 1 - REMOVED FROM HEARTBEAT)\n# Vector flush should NOT run on every heartbeat. It should only run:\n# 1) On-demand when semantic retrieval is needed\n# 2) Scheduled via cron once or twice per day  \n# 3) After meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion)\n# This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773079430367}}
{"type":"message","id":"14709db9","parentId":"b64376a9","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:03:55.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll execute the workspace-janitor skill. According to AGENTS.md, I should read the skill's SKILL.md file first."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0Ya0Gt86QbgIMPnvn4MFM8di","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/workspace-janitor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":269,"output":90,"cacheRead":14528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14887,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773079430369}}
{"type":"message","id":"9aa8f8ec","parentId":"14709db9","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:03:55.637Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_0Ya0Gt86QbgIMPnvn4MFM8di","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: workspace-janitor\ndescription: Safe workspace maintenance skill that scans, classifies, and proposes cleanup of obsolete files with user authorization.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: workspace-janitor\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\", \"python\"]\nsafety-level: high\n---\n\n# workspace-janitor\n\n## Purpose\nMaintain, clean, and organize the OpenClaw workspace directory with extreme safety hardening. The skill analyzes the entire `workspace/` directory, identifies unused/obsolete/temporary files, protects system files and active skills, maintains a deletion candidate registry, asks for explicit user authorization before deletion, and generates a clean workspace structure.\n\n## Safety Hardening (CRITICAL)\nThe janitor must NEVER delete automatically. Deletion requires:\n1. Candidate identification\n2. Logging\n3. User confirmation\n4. Safe removal\n\n**Protected zones (NEVER delete):**\n- `workspace/skills/`\n- `workspace/references/`\n- `workspace/memory/`\n- `workspace/.learnings/`\n- `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`\n\nAny attempt to modify protected zones must trigger: `janitor|PROTECTED_PATH|blocked`\n\n## Cleanup Targets\nThe janitor may analyze and mark candidates inside:\n- `workspace/projects/`\n- `workspace/temp_refs/`\n- `workspace/*.tmp`\n- `workspace/temp_*`\n- Files matching patterns: `temp_process*`, `analysis_*.json`, `*_old.py`, `*_backup*`, `temp_*.md`\n\n## Expiration Policy\n- Project temporary files older than 30 days → cleanup candidates\n- Skill run artifacts older than 14 days → may be archived\n- Temporary debug files older than 7 days → deletion candidates\n- Policies must be configurable (via `janitor_config.json`)\n\n## Janitor Logbook\nMaintain `workspace/memory/janitor_log.md` with records:\n- Candidate file path\n- File type\n- Last modified date\n- Why considered obsolete\n- Risk level\n- Recommended action\n\n## Deletion Authorization Workflow\nBefore deleting anything, present `JANITOR_CLEANUP_REPORT.md` including:\n- Files flagged\n- Size impact\n- Reason for removal\n- Risk classification\nThen ask: \"Authorize cleanup?\" Only after explicit approval may deletion occur.\n\n## Workspace Classification Engine\nImplement classification system:\n- SAFE (protected zone, never delete)\n- SYSTEM (configuration files, never delete)\n- TEMPORARY (likely safe to delete after expiration)\n- PROJECT_ARTIFACT (project temporary files, may delete after expiration)\n- UNKNOWN (must NEVER be deleted automatically, escalate to user)\n\n## Cron Job Integration\nIf OpenClaw cron scheduling is available, support scheduled maintenance:\n- Daily: scan workspace, update janitor_log.md\n- Weekly: generate cleanup report\n- Monthly: propose cleanup candidates\nCron may ONLY trigger scan and report generation, NEVER automatic deletion.\n\n## Required Scripts\nThe skill includes the following Python scripts in `scripts/`:\n- `scan_workspace.py`: walk workspace, produce inventory JSON\n- `classify_files.py`: classify each file based on path, name, extension\n- `detect_expired_files.py`: apply expiration policies to classify candidates\n- `generate_cleanup_report.py`: generate human-readable report\n- `janitor_delete.py`: perform safe deletion after user approval\n- `janitor_utils.py`: common utilities (path validation, logging, config)\n\n## Runtime Flow\n1. **Stage 1 — Workspace Scan**: Scan workspace directory, generate `workspace_inventory.json`\n2. **Stage 2 — File Classification**: Classify every file, generate `workspace_classification.json`\n3. **Stage 3 — Expiration Detection**: Detect expired files using policies, generate `cleanup_candidates.json`\n4. **Stage 4 — Report Generation**: Generate `JANITOR_CLEANUP_REPORT.md`\n5. **Stage 5 — Authorization**: Request explicit user approval\n6. **Stage 6 — Safe Deletion**: If approved, delete files and update `janitor_log.md`\n\n## Usage\nManual invocation:\n`workspace-janitor` – run full workflow (scan, classify, report, ask for approval)\n`workspace-janitor scan` – only scan and classify, no deletion\n`workspace-janitor report` – generate cleanup report from existing classification\n`workspace-janitor clean` – proceed with deletion (requires previous approval)\n\n## Configuration\nCreate `workspace/memory/janitor_config.json` with customizable expiration thresholds and protected patterns.\n\n## Examples\nSee `examples/example_cleanup_report.md` for sample output.\n\n## Safety Checks\n- Verify absolute path is within workspace before any file operation.\n- Ensure protected zones are never touched.\n- Log every action to `janitor_log.md`.\n- Require interactive confirmation for deletions.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773079435633}}
